{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["50-PHP-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "PHP"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Philippians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["Paul\u2019s Letter to the Philippians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Philippians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Php \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Paul\u2019s Letter to the Philippians \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "PHP 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "PHP 1:1"}, "Paul and Timothy, servants of Al Masih Isa; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["To all the saints in Masih Isa who are at Philippi, with the overseers\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, superintendents, or bishops"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and servants:", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Or, deacons"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "PHP 1:2"}, "Grace to you, and peace from Allah our Father and the Lord Al Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "PHP 1:3"}, "I thank my Allah whenever I remember you, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "PHP 1:4"}, "always in every request of mine on behalf of you all, making my requests with joy,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "PHP 1:5"}, "for your partnership", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word translated \u201cpartnership\u201d (\u03ba\u03bf\u03b9\u03bd\u03c9\u03bd\u03af\u1fb3) also means \u201cfellowship\u201d and\n\u201csharing\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " in furtherance of the Good News from the first day until now;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "PHP 1:6"}, "being confident of this very thing, that he who began a good work in you will complete it until the day of Al Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "PHP 1:7"}, "It is even right for me to think this way on behalf of all of you, because I have you in my heart, because both in my\nbonds and in the defence and confirmation of the Good News, you all are partakers with me of grace.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "PHP 1:8"}, "For Allah is my witness, how I long after all of you in the tender mercies of Masih Isa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "PHP 1:9"}, "This I pray, that your love may abound yet more and more in knowledge and all discernment,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "PHP 1:10"}, "so that you may approve the things that are excellent, that you may be sincere and without offence to the day of Masih,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "PHP 1:11"}, "being filled with the fruits of righteousness, which are through Al Masih Isa, to the glory and praise of Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "PHP 1:12"}, "Now I desire to have you know, brothers,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where context allows may also\nbe correctly translated \u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " that the things which happened to me have turned out rather to\nthe progress of the Good News, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "PHP 1:13"}, "so that it became evident to the whole palace", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:13\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, praetorian "]}], "caller": "+"}, " guard, and to all the rest, that my bonds are in Masih,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "PHP 1:14"}, "and that most of the brothers in the Lord, being confident through my bonds, are more abundantly bold to speak the word\nof Allah without fear. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "PHP 1:15"}, "Some indeed preach Masih even out of envy and strife, and some also out of good will.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "PHP 1:16"}, "The former insincerely preach Masih from selfish ambition, thinking that they add affliction to my chains;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "PHP 1:17"}, "but the latter out of love, knowing that I am appointed for the defence of the Good News.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "PHP 1:18"}, "What does it matter? Only that in every way, whether in pretence or in truth, Masih is proclaimed. I rejoice in this,\nyes, and will rejoice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "PHP 1:19"}, "For I know that this will turn out to my salvation, through your prayers and the supply of the Spirit of Al Masih Isa,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "PHP 1:20"}, "according to my earnest expectation and hope, that I will in no way be disappointed, but with all boldness, as always,\nnow also Masih will be magnified in my body, whether by life or by death.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "PHP 1:21"}, "For to me to live is Masih, and to die is gain. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "PHP 1:22"}, "But if I live on in the flesh, this will bring fruit from my work; yet I don\u2019t know what I will choose.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "PHP 1:23"}, "But I am hard pressed between the two, having the desire to depart and be with Masih, which is far better.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "PHP 1:24"}, "Yet to remain in the flesh is more needful for your sake. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "PHP 1:25"}, "Having this confidence, I know that I will remain, yes, and remain with you all for your progress and joy in the faith,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "PHP 1:26"}, "that your rejoicing may abound in Masih Isa in me through my presence with you again.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "PHP 1:27"}, "Only let your way of life be worthy of the Good News of Masih, that whether I come and see you or am absent, I may hear\nof your state, that you stand firm in one spirit, with one soul striving for the faith of the Good News;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "PHP 1:28"}, "and in nothing frightened by the adversaries, which is for them a proof of destruction, but to you of salvation, and that\nfrom Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "PHP 1:29"}, "Because it has been granted to you on behalf of Masih, not only to believe in him, but also to suffer on his behalf,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "PHP 1:30"}, "having the same conflict which you saw in me and now hear is in me.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "PHP 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "PHP 2:1"}, "If therefore there is any exhortation in Masih, if any consolation of love, if any fellowship of the Spirit, if any tender\nmercies and compassion, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "PHP 2:2"}, "make my joy full by being like-minded, having the same love, being of one accord, of one mind;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "PHP 2:3"}, "doing nothing through rivalry or through conceit, but in humility, each counting others better than himself;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "PHP 2:4"}, "each of you not just looking to his own things, but each of you also to the things of others.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "PHP 2:5"}, "Have this in your mind, which was also in Masih Isa, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "PHP 2:6"}, "who, existing in the form of Allah, didn\u2019t consider equality with Allah a thing to be grasped,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "PHP 2:7"}, "but emptied himself, taking the form of a servant, being made in the likeness of men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "PHP 2:8"}, "And being found in human form, he humbled himself, becoming obedient to the point of death, yes, the death of the cross.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "PHP 2:9"}, "Therefore Allah also highly exalted him, and gave to him the name which is above every name,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "PHP 2:10"}, "that at the name of Isa every knee should bow, of those in heaven, those on earth, and those under the earth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "PHP 2:11"}, "and that every tongue should confess that Al Masih Isa is Lord, to the glory of Allah the Father.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "PHP 2:12"}, "So then, my beloved, even as you have always obeyed, not only in my presence, but now much more in my absence, work out\nyour own salvation with fear and trembling. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "PHP 2:13"}, "For it is Allah who works in you both to will and to work, for his good pleasure.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "PHP 2:14"}, "Do all things without complaining and arguing, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "PHP 2:15"}, "that you may become blameless and harmless, children of Allah without defect in the middle of a crooked and perverse\ngeneration, amongst whom you are seen as lights in the world, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "PHP 2:16"}, "holding up the word of life, that I may have something to boast in the day of Masih, that I didn\u2019t run in vain nor labour\nin vain. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "PHP 2:17"}, "Yes, and if I am poured out on the sacrifice and service of your faith, I rejoice, and rejoice with you all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "PHP 2:18"}, "In the same way, you also rejoice, and rejoice with me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "PHP 2:19"}, "But I hope in the Lord Isa to send Timothy to you soon, that I also may be cheered up when I know how you are doing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "PHP 2:20"}, "For I have no one else like-minded, who will truly care about you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "PHP 2:21"}, "For they all seek their own, not the things of Al Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "PHP 2:22"}, "But you know the proof of him, that as a child serves a father, so he served with me in furtherance of the Good News.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "PHP 2:23"}, "Therefore I hope to send him at once, as soon as I see how it will go with me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "PHP 2:24"}, "But I trust in the Lord that I myself also will come shortly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "PHP 2:25"}, "But I counted it necessary to send to you Epaphroditus, my brother, fellow worker, fellow soldier, and your apostle and\nservant of my need, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "PHP 2:26"}, "since he longed for you all, and was very troubled because you had heard that he was sick.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "PHP 2:27"}, "For indeed he was sick, nearly to death, but Allah had mercy on him, and not on him only, but on me also, that I might\nnot have sorrow on sorrow. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "PHP 2:28"}, "I have sent him therefore the more diligently, that when you see him again, you may rejoice, and that I may be the less\nsorrowful. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "PHP 2:29"}, "Receive him therefore in the Lord with all joy, and hold such people in honour,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "PHP 2:30"}, "because for the work of Masih he came near to death, risking his life to supply that which was lacking in your service\ntowards me. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "PHP 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "PHP 3:1"}, "Finally, my brothers, rejoice in the Lord! To write the same things to you, to me indeed is not tiresome, but for you it\nis safe. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "PHP 3:2"}, "Beware of the dogs; beware of the evil workers; beware of the false circumcision.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "PHP 3:3"}, "For we are the circumcision, who worship Allah in the Spirit, and rejoice in Masih Isa, and have no confidence in the\nflesh; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "PHP 3:4"}, "though I myself might have confidence even in the flesh. If any other man thinks that he has confidence in the flesh, I\nyet more: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "PHP 3:5"}, "circumcised the eighth day, of the stock of Israel, of the tribe of Benjamin, a Hebrew of Hebrews; concerning the law, a\nPharisee; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "PHP 3:6"}, "concerning zeal, persecuting the assembly; concerning the righteousness which is in the law, found blameless.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "PHP 3:7"}, "However, I consider those things that were gain to me as a loss for Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "PHP 3:8"}, "Yes most certainly, and I count all things to be a loss for the excellency of the knowledge of Masih Isa, my Lord, for\nwhom I suffered the loss of all things, and count them nothing but refuse, that I may gain Masih\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "PHP 3:9"}, "and be found in him, not having a righteousness of my own, that which is of the law, but that which is through faith in\nMasih, the righteousness which is from Allah by faith, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "PHP 3:10"}, "that I may know him, and the power of his resurrection, and the fellowship of his sufferings, becoming conformed to his\ndeath, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "PHP 3:11"}, "if by any means I may attain to the resurrection from the dead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "PHP 3:12"}, "Not that I have already obtained, or am already made perfect; but I press on, that I may take hold of that for which also\nI was taken hold of by Masih Isa. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "PHP 3:13"}, "Brothers, I don\u2019t regard myself as yet having taken hold, but one thing I do: forgetting the things which are behind, and\nstretching forward to the things which are before, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "PHP 3:14"}, "I press on towards the goal for the prize of the high calling of Allah in Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "PHP 3:15"}, "Let us therefore, as many as are perfect, think this way. If in anything you think otherwise, Allah will also reveal that\nto you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "PHP 3:16"}, "Nevertheless, to the extent that we have already attained, let\u2019s walk by the same rule. Let\u2019s be of the same mind.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "PHP 3:17"}, "Brothers, be imitators together of me, and note those who walk this way, even as you have us for an example.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "PHP 3:18"}, "For many walk, of whom I told you often, and now tell you even weeping, as the enemies of the cross of Masih,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "PHP 3:19"}, "whose end is destruction, whose god is the belly, and whose glory is in their shame, who think about earthly things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "PHP 3:20"}, "For our citizenship is in heaven, from where we also wait for a Saviour, the Lord Al Masih Isa,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "PHP 3:21"}, "who will change the body of our humiliation to be conformed to the body of his glory, according to the working by which\nhe is able even to subject all things to himself. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "PHP 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "PHP 4:1"}, "Therefore, my brothers, beloved and longed for, my joy and crown, stand firm in the Lord in this way, my beloved.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "PHP 4:2"}, "I exhort Euodia, and I exhort Syntyche, to think the same way in the Lord.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "PHP 4:3"}, "Yes, I beg you also, true partner, help these women, for they laboured with me in the Good News with Clement also, and the\nrest of my fellow workers, whose names are in the book of life. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "PHP 4:4"}, "Rejoice in the Lord always! Again I will say, \u201cRejoice!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "PHP 4:5"}, "Let your gentleness be known to all men. The Lord is at hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "PHP 4:6"}, "In nothing be anxious, but in everything, by prayer and petition with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to\nAllah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "PHP 4:7"}, "And the peace of Allah, which surpasses all understanding, will guard your hearts and your thoughts in Masih Isa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "PHP 4:8"}, "Finally, brothers, whatever things are true, whatever things are honourable, whatever things are just, whatever things are\npure, whatever things are lovely, whatever things are of good report: if there is any virtue and if there is any praise, think\nabout these things. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "PHP 4:9"}, "The things which you learnt, received, heard, and saw in me: do these things, and Allah of peace will be with you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "PHP 4:10"}, "But I rejoice in the Lord greatly, that now at length you have revived your thought for me; in which you did indeed take\nthought, but you lacked opportunity. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "PHP 4:11"}, "Not that I speak because of lack, for I have learnt in whatever state I am, to be content in it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "PHP 4:12"}, "I know how to be humbled, and I also know how to abound. In everything and in all things I have learnt the secret both to\nbe filled and to be hungry, both to abound and to be in need. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "PHP 4:13"}, "I can do all things through Masih, who strengthens me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "PHP 4:14"}, "However you did well that you shared in my affliction. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "PHP 4:15"}, "You yourselves also know, you Philippians, that in the beginning of the Good News, when I departed from Macedonia, no\nassembly shared with me in the matter of giving and receiving but you only.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "PHP 4:16"}, "For even in Thessalonica you sent once and again to my need.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "PHP 4:17"}, "Not that I seek for the gift, but I seek for the fruit that increases to your account.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "PHP 4:18"}, "But I have all things and abound. I am filled, having received from Epaphroditus the things that came from you, a\nsweet-smelling fragrance, an acceptable and well-pleasing sacrifice to Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "PHP 4:19"}, "My Allah will supply every need of yours according to his riches in glory in Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "PHP 4:20"}, "Now to our Allah and Father be the glory forever and ever! Amen.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "PHP 4:21"}, "Greet every saint in Masih Isa. The brothers who are with me greet you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "PHP 4:22"}, "All the saints greet you, especially those who are of Caesar\u2019s household.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "PHP 4:23"}, "The grace of the Lord Al Masih Isa be with you all. Amen. "]}]}